Hi everyone,

Below is the agenda for Daily Controls Monitoring KT – Part 2. This session will be more hands-on and focused on performing actual analysis using real examples.

Agenda

1. Quick Recap (5 mins)  
   - Review of Daily DQC monitoring objectives  
   - End-to-end workflow reminder (detect → understand → document → escalate → track)

2. Hands-On Failure Review (25 mins)  
   - Walk through real daily control failures  
   - Review logs and supporting evidence  
   - Identify root cause and determine ownership (upstream vs TechADS vs downstream)

3. RCA Documentation & Tracking (15 mins)  
   - How to fill out failure comments consistently  
   - When to exclude vs include failures  
   - Creating and tracking Jira stories for remediation

4. Tools & References Deep Dive (10 mins)  
   - Daily DQ app vs spreadsheet usage  
   - Where to find queries, config tables, and documentation  
   - Tips for common failure patterns

5. Q&A / Next Steps (5 mins)  
   - Open questions  
   - Expectations going forward  
   - Preview of upcoming KT sessions (PARCM tie-in, EIQ, automation)

Let me know if there are any topics you’d like to make sure we cover.

Thanks,  
Kamran